/ (root)
├─ index.html           → **Home**
│   Hero section with your name & tagline  
│   Brief overview of services/expertise  
│   CTA buttons: “View Services” → /services, “Contact Me” → /contact
│
├─ services/            → **Services**
│   Technical & Automation: CRM setup, workflow automation, integrations  
│   QA & Functional Testing: Websites, landing pages, CRM workflows  
│   Project & Operations Management: Project planning, client support
│
├─ core-skills/         → **Core Skills**
│   CRM & Automation: GoHighLevel, Pabbly  
│   Project Management: ClickUp  
│   QA & Testing: Functional & performance QA  
│   Web & System Support: Backend configuration, workflow troubleshooting
│
├─ portfolio/           → **Portfolio / Projects**
│   Showcase technical projects, CRM setups, workflow automation, QA results  
│   Include screenshots, case studies, or live project links
│
├─ testimonials/        → **Testimonials**
│   Client reviews, success stories, and measurable results
│
├─ contact/             → **Contact**
│   Inquiry form for clients/projects  
│   Email and social media links  
│   Optional CTA linking to Little Things brand → /littlethings
│
├─ careers/             → **Freelance / Career Opportunities**
│   Entry-Level Roles: System Engineer, CRM Assistant, Junior Project Coordinator, Technical Support  
│   Mid-Level Roles: Project Lead / Manager, Customer Success Manager, QA Analyst, Operations Manager
│
├─ target-clients/      → **Target Clients**
│   Startups / SMEs needing automation  
│   Companies requiring CRM & workflow solutions  
│   Technical projects requiring QA & operations management
│
├─ about/               → **About**
│   Bio and professional story  
│   Mission & approach  
│   Highlights of expertise  
│   Optional personal touch: photo, quote, philosophy
│
├─ footer/              → **Footer**
│   Quick links to all pages  
│   Copyright info  
│   Social media / GitHub links
│
└─ .nojekyll            → Disables GitHub Pages Jekyll processing  
                          (empty file, ensures folder/files with underscores are served properly)
